<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E51C51EFF3FBD88FCFCEF97" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E51C51EFF3FBD88FCFCEF97" blockId="83.[151,1436,595,1016]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFF3FBD88FE97EFDF" bold="true" box="[199,321,667,692]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
With orange pronotum and dark brown elytra; without flashing data; very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E51C51EFAE8BD8EFA4AEFDF" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1296,1436,668,692]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effulgens">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFAE8BD8EFA4AEFDF" box="[1296,1436,668,692]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">M. effulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFF3DBDD2FE85EFB3" box="[197,339,704,728]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E51C51EFF3DBDD2FE99EFB3" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[197,335,704,728]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminea">M. fulminea</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
(both of which have associated flashing data), distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E51C51EFBCFBDD2FB16EFB3" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1079,1216,704,728]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effulgens">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFBCFBDD2FB16EFB3" box="[1079,1216,704,728]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">M. effulgens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the brown head, and from 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E51C51EFEFCBDF6FE5DEF97" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[260,395,740,764]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminea">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFEFCBDF6FE5DEF97" box="[260,395,740,764]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">M. fulminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its distribution in the 
<collectingCountry id="14D103905E51C51EFD5CBDF7FCF0EF97" box="[676,806,740,764]" name="Philippines" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E51C51EFF3FBC1BFEC6EE93" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E51C51EFF3FBC1BFE0DEE0C" blockId="83.[151,1436,595,1016]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFF3FBC1BFEEDEE4B" bold="true" box="[199,315,776,800]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previously it was considered that bent-winged fireflies without the MFC were restricted to New 
<collectingCountry id="14D103905E51C51EFF6FBC3FFF3EEE2F" box="[151,232,812,836]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry id="14D103905E51C51EFE7FBC3FFE38EE2F" box="[391,494,812,836]" name="Australia" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E51C51EFE05BC3FFD06EE2F" author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[509,720,812,836]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne, 1987a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E51C51EFD1CBC3EFC80EE2F" authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1976" box="[740,854,812,836]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amilae">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFD1CBC3EFC80EE2F" box="[740,854,812,836]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">M. amilae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the first species without the comb recorded west of the island of New 
<collectingCountry id="14D103905E51C51EFE7ABC5CFE01EE0C" box="[386,471,847,871]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Guinea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7943005E51C51EFF3FBC67FEC6EE93" blockId="83.[151,1436,595,1016]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
The head colour between the eyes of the 
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E51C51EFD6DBC67FD21EEE7" box="[661,759,884,908]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">holotype</typeStatus>
as interpreted by LB is medium brown (Satô described it as yellow orange). This colour is characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E51C51EFD45BC8AFC91EEDB" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[701,839,920,944]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminea">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFD45BC8AFC91EEDB" box="[701,839,920,944]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">M. fulminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is retained because it is based on Behaviour Voucher specimens where accurate light patterns are related to individual specimens. No such data is available for 
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E51C51EFF6FBCF2FEC6EE93" box="[151,272,992,1016]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E51C51EFF6FBCF2FEDAEE93" authorityName="Sato" authorityYear="1976" box="[151,268,992,1016]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amilae">M. amilae</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
